Cell.Text: [S] So you're interested in my potions and ingredients?
[S] Got a pretty full stock of potions and alchemy reagents.
[S] Ah, so you're an alchemist, then?
[S] The finest weapons and armor.
[S] Hmm... Blades, helmets. Pretty much anything to suit your needs.
[S] Looking to protect yourself, or deal some damage?
What'll you give me for these?
[S] Usual guild rate. Let's take a look at them.
What'll you give me for these?
[S] Why don't you take a look at some of my merchandise and we'll see what kind of a deal we can make.
What'll you give me for these?
[S] I've got coin and I've got merchandise. Let's see what we can do.
What'll you give me for these?
[S] I give special rates to members of the Thieves Guild. Show me what you've got.
[S] Bow and arrows for the mighty huntsman.
[S] An archer, eh? Oh, I've got just what you need.
[S] What are you hunting? Never mind. I don't want to know.
[S] Drink for the thirsty, food for the hungry.
[S] Let's sate that appetite, hmm?
What's on the menu?
[S] Depends. Are you thirsty, hungry, both?
[S] Beautiful things for beautiful people.
[S] Let see what adornments I might have available...
[S] I've got some wonderful jewelry.
[S] Oh, a bit of this and a bit of that.
[S] Trinkets, odds and ends, that sort of thing.
[S] Some may call this junk. Me, I call them treasures.
[S] Spells and incantations for those with the talent to cast them.
[S] So, you wish to master the arcane arts...
[S] Hmph. I had you figured for a mage. I think you'll appreciate this...
[S] Clothes and raiment for the discerning customer.
[S] Breeches, gowns... clothes for any occasion, really.
[S] Let's see if we can't find an outfit that suits you.
[S] Take a look.
